            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EJesus%20spent%20His%20life%20bearing%20the%20insults%20of%20those%20who%20insulted%20God.%20King%20Hezekiah's%20messengers%20received%20much%20the%20same%20reaction%20in%20the%20tribes%20of%20Israel%20when%20they%20presented%20the%20invitation%20to%20return%20to%20the%20Lord%20and%20celebrate%20Passover%20(2%20Chronicles%2030%3A10).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ETo%20the%20backslidden%20Israelites%2C%20the%20archaic%20idea%20of%20a%20Passover%20in%20Jerusalem%20was%20absurd.%20The%20messengers%20sincerely%20tried%20to%20turn%20the%20Israelites'%20hearts%20back%20to%20God%2C%20but%20the%20results%20were%20the%20same%20in%20village%20after%20village%3A%20%22But%20most%20of%20the%20people%20just%20laughed%20at%20the%20messengers%20and%20made%20fun%20of%20them%22%20(v.%2010).%20However%2C%20the%20Scripture%20records%20that%20%22some%20.%20.%20.%20humbled%20themselves%20and%20went%20to%20Jerusalem%22%20(v.%2011).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIf%20we%20just%20want%20to%20please%20ourselves%2C%20we%20will%20not%20venture%20out%20into%20the%20stream%20of%20evangelism%20where%20our%20feelings%20may%20get%20hurt.%20The%20burden%20of%20evangelism%2C%20however%2C%20belongs%20to%20God%2C%20and%20if%20we%20love%20Him%2C%20we%20will%20be%20willing%20to%20%22bear%20the%20disgrace%20he%20bore%22%20(Hebrews%2013%3A13).%20We%20must%20realize%20that%20we%20are%20simply%20messengers%20delivering%20an%20invitation%20that%20others%20can%20either%20accept%20or%20reject.%20If%20Jesus%20was%20reproached%2C%20so%20must%20we%20be.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ERejoice%20if%20men%20ridicule%20you.%20You%20are%20bearing%20the%20insults%20of%20God!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "2Chr.30:1-31:21",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E2%20Chronicles%2030%3A1-31%3A21%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E30%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EPreparations%20for%20Passover%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EKing%20Hezekiah%20now%20sent%20word%20to%20all%20Israel%20and%20Judah%2C%20and%20he%20wrote%20letters%20of%20invitation%20to%20the%20people%20of%20Ephraim%20and%20Manasseh.%20He%20asked%20everyone%20to%20come%20to%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20at%20Jerusalem%20to%20celebrate%20the%20Passover%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20king%2C%20his%20officials%2C%20and%20all%20the%20community%20of%20Jerusalem%20decided%20to%20celebrate%20Passover%20a%20month%20later%20than%20usual.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E30%3A2%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ein%20the%20second%20month.%3C%2Fem%3E%20Passover%20was%20normally%20observed%20in%20the%20first%20month%20(of%20the%20ancient%20Hebrew%20lunar%20calendar).%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20were%20unable%20to%20celebrate%20it%20at%20the%20prescribed%20time%20because%20not%20enough%20priests%20could%20be%20purified%20by%20then%2C%20and%20the%20people%20had%20not%20yet%20assembled%20at%20Jerusalem.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20plan%20for%20keeping%20the%20Passover%20seemed%20right%20to%20the%20king%20and%20all%20the%20people.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20they%20sent%20a%20proclamation%20throughout%20all%20Israel%2C%20from%20Beersheba%20in%20the%20south%20to%20Dan%20in%20the%20north%2C%20inviting%20everyone%20to%20come%20to%20Jerusalem%20to%20celebrate%20the%20Passover%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel.%20The%20people%20had%20not%20been%20celebrating%20it%20in%20great%20numbers%20as%20required%20in%20the%20Law.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EAt%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20command%2C%20runners%20were%20sent%20throughout%20Israel%20and%20Judah.%20They%20carried%20letters%20that%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body-fl-sp%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BO%26%23xA0%3Bpeople%20of%20Israel%2C%20return%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Abraham%2C%20Isaac%2C%20and%20Israel%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E30%3A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cem%3EIsrael%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20the%20name%20that%20God%20gave%20to%20Jacob.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20so%20that%20he%20will%20return%20to%20the%20few%20of%20us%20who%20have%20survived%20the%20conquest%20of%20the%20Assyrian%20kings.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EDo%20not%20be%20like%20your%20ancestors%20and%20relatives%20who%20abandoned%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20their%20ancestors%2C%20and%20became%20an%20object%20of%20derision%2C%20as%20you%20yourselves%20can%20see.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_8%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EDo%20not%20be%20stubborn%2C%20as%20they%20were%2C%20but%20submit%20yourselves%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20Come%20to%20his%20Temple%2C%20which%20he%20has%20set%20apart%20as%20holy%20forever.%20Worship%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God%20so%20that%20his%20fierce%20anger%20will%20turn%20away%20from%20you.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_9%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BFor%20if%20you%20return%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20your%20relatives%20and%20your%20children%20will%20be%20treated%20mercifully%20by%20their%20captors%2C%20and%20they%20will%20be%20able%20to%20return%20to%20this%20land.%20For%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20your%20God%20is%20gracious%20and%20merciful.%20If%20you%20return%20to%20him%2C%20he%20will%20not%20continue%20to%20turn%20his%20face%20from%20you.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_10%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ECelebration%20of%20Passover%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20runners%20went%20from%20town%20to%20town%20throughout%20Ephraim%20and%20Manasseh%20and%20as%20far%20as%20the%20territory%20of%20Zebulun.%20But%20most%20of%20the%20people%20just%20laughed%20at%20the%20runners%20and%20made%20fun%20of%20them.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_11%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EHowever%2C%20some%20people%20from%20Asher%2C%20Manasseh%2C%20and%20Zebulun%20humbled%20themselves%20and%20went%20to%20Jerusalem.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_12%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20God%26%23x2019%3Bs%20hand%20was%20on%20the%20people%20in%20the%20land%20of%20Judah%2C%20giving%20them%20all%20one%20heart%20to%20obey%20the%20orders%20of%20the%20king%20and%20his%20officials%2C%20who%20were%20following%20the%20word%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_13%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20a%20huge%20crowd%20assembled%20at%20Jerusalem%20in%20midspring%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E30%3A13%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ein%20the%20second%20month.%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20second%20month%20of%20the%20ancient%20Hebrew%20lunar%20calendar%20usually%20occurs%20within%20the%20months%20of%20April%20and%20May.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20to%20celebrate%20the%20Festival%20of%20Unleavened%20Bread.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_14%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20set%20to%20work%20and%20removed%20the%20pagan%20altars%20from%20Jerusalem.%20They%20took%20away%20all%20the%20incense%20altars%20and%20threw%20them%20into%20the%20Kidron%20Valley.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_15%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EOn%20the%20fourteenth%20day%20of%20the%20second%20month%2C%20one%20month%20later%20than%20usual%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E30%3A15%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EOn%20the%20fourteenth%20day%20of%20the%20second%20month.%3C%2Fem%3E%20Passover%20normally%20began%20on%20the%20fourteenth%20day%20of%20the%20first%20month%20(see%20Lev%2023%3A5).%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20people%20slaughtered%20the%20Passover%20lamb.%20This%20shamed%20the%20priests%20and%20Levites%2C%20so%20they%20purified%20themselves%20and%20brought%20burnt%20offerings%20to%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_16%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20they%20took%20their%20places%20at%20the%20Temple%20as%20prescribed%20in%20the%20Law%20of%20Moses%2C%20the%20man%20of%20God.%20The%20Levites%20brought%20the%20sacrificial%20blood%20to%20the%20priests%2C%20who%20then%20sprinkled%20it%20on%20the%20altar.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_17%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3ESince%20many%20of%20the%20people%20had%20not%20purified%20themselves%2C%20the%20Levites%20had%20to%20slaughter%20their%20Passover%20lamb%20for%20them%2C%20to%20set%20them%20apart%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_18%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EMost%20of%20those%20who%20came%20from%20Ephraim%2C%20Manasseh%2C%20Issachar%2C%20and%20Zebulun%20had%20not%20purified%20themselves.%20But%20King%20Hezekiah%20prayed%20for%20them%2C%20and%20they%20were%20allowed%20to%20eat%20the%20Passover%20meal%20anyway%2C%20even%20though%20this%20was%20contrary%20to%20the%20requirements%20of%20the%20Law.%20For%20Hezekiah%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BMay%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20who%20is%20good%2C%20pardon%20those%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_19%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3Ewho%20decide%20to%20follow%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20their%20ancestors%2C%20even%20though%20they%20are%20not%20properly%20cleansed%20for%20the%20ceremony.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_20%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20listened%20to%20Hezekiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20prayer%20and%20healed%20the%20people.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_21%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20the%20people%20of%20Israel%20who%20were%20present%20in%20Jerusalem%20joyously%20celebrated%20the%20Festival%20of%20Unleavened%20Bread%20for%20seven%20days.%20Each%20day%20the%20Levites%20and%20priests%20sang%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20accompanied%20by%20loud%20instruments.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E30%3A21%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Esang%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ci%20class%3D%22tn-sc-ital%22%3ELord%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cem%3E%20with%20all%20their%20strength.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_22%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EHezekiah%20encouraged%20all%20the%20Levites%20regarding%20the%20skill%20they%20displayed%20as%20they%20served%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20The%20celebration%20continued%20for%20seven%20days.%20Peace%20offerings%20were%20sacrificed%2C%20and%20the%20people%20gave%20thanks%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20their%20ancestors.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_23%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20entire%20assembly%20then%20decided%20to%20continue%20the%20festival%20another%20seven%20days%2C%20so%20they%20celebrated%20joyfully%20for%20another%20week.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_24%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3EKing%20Hezekiah%20gave%20the%20people%201%2C000%20bulls%20and%207%2C000%20sheep%20and%20goats%20for%20offerings%2C%20and%20the%20officials%20donated%201%2C000%20bulls%20and%2010%2C000%20sheep%20and%20goats.%20Meanwhile%2C%20many%20more%20priests%20purified%20themselves.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_25%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20entire%20assembly%20of%20Judah%20rejoiced%2C%20including%20the%20priests%2C%20the%20Levites%2C%20all%20who%20came%20from%20the%20land%20of%20Israel%2C%20the%20foreigners%20who%20came%20to%20the%20festival%2C%20and%20all%20those%20who%20lived%20in%20Judah.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_26%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E26%3C%2Fspan%3EThere%20was%20great%20joy%20in%20the%20city%2C%20for%20Jerusalem%20had%20not%20seen%20a%20celebration%20like%20this%20one%20since%20the%20days%20of%20Solomon%2C%20King%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20son.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_30_27%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2230%22%20vn%3D%2227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E27%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20priests%20and%20Levites%20stood%20and%20blessed%20the%20people%2C%20and%20God%20heard%20their%20prayer%20from%20his%20holy%20dwelling%20in%20heaven.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_31_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2231%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E31%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EHezekiah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Religious%20Reforms%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20the%20festival%20ended%2C%20the%20Israelites%20who%20attended%20went%20to%20all%20the%20towns%20of%20Judah%2C%20Benjamin%2C%20Ephraim%2C%20and%20Manasseh%2C%20and%20they%20smashed%20all%20the%20sacred%20pillars%2C%20cut%20down%20the%20Asherah%20poles%2C%20and%20removed%20the%20pagan%20shrines%20and%20altars.%20After%20this%2C%20the%20Israelites%20returned%20to%20their%20own%20towns%20and%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_31_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2231%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EHezekiah%20then%20organized%20the%20priests%20and%20Levites%20into%20divisions%20to%20offer%20the%20burnt%20offerings%20and%20peace%20offerings%2C%20and%20to%20worship%20and%20give%20thanks%20and%20praise%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20at%20the%20gates%20of%20the%20Temple.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_31_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2231%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20king%20also%20made%20a%20personal%20contribution%20of%20animals%20for%20the%20daily%20morning%20and%20evening%20burnt%20offerings%2C%20the%20weekly%20Sabbath%20festivals%2C%20the%20monthly%20new%20moon%20festivals%2C%20and%20the%20annual%20festivals%20as%20prescribed%20in%20the%20Law%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_31_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2231%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20addition%2C%20he%20required%20the%20people%20in%20Jerusalem%20to%20bring%20a%20portion%20of%20their%20goods%20to%20the%20priests%20and%20Levites%2C%20so%20they%20could%20devote%20themselves%20fully%20to%20the%20Law%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_31_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2231%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20the%20people%20of%20Israel%20heard%20these%20requirements%2C%20they%20responded%20generously%20by%20bringing%20the%20first%20share%20of%20their%20grain%2C%20new%20wine%2C%20olive%20oil%2C%20honey%2C%20and%20all%20the%20produce%20of%20their%20fields.%20They%20brought%20a%20large%20quantity%26%23x2014%3Ba%20tithe%20of%20all%20they%20produced.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_31_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2231%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20people%20who%20had%20moved%20to%20Judah%20from%20Israel%2C%20and%20the%20people%20of%20Judah%20themselves%2C%20brought%20in%20the%20tithes%20of%20their%20cattle%2C%20sheep%2C%20and%20goats%20and%20a%20tithe%20of%20the%20things%20that%20had%20been%20dedicated%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20their%20God%2C%20and%20they%20piled%20them%20up%20in%20great%20heaps.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_31_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2231%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20began%20piling%20them%20up%20in%20late%20spring%2C%20and%20the%20heaps%2